Writing Images

*As I sat in the dimly lit room, the smell of old books and dusty photographs filled the air. The sounds of the city outside faded away, replaced by the soft hum of the fluorescent lights above. I felt a sense of calm wash over me as I opened the worn leather journal, the pages crackling with age.*
